<L>__{exterior forest day}
<A>__{they are travelling together now, on either side of the horse's nose, finding comfort in the closeness of each other. they stop for bobby to consult his compass. he indicates a slight change of direction, and they move off again. still they don't talk. we can feel their anxiety breeding in the silence. why don't they talk? they proceed in this weighty silence, but even the cries of the birds now seem to mock them. the route takes them downhill. the slopes are more dense with undergrowth now and the going isn't so easy. some times they are reduced to an undignified scramble, hanging onto the bulk of the horse between them. they no longer look much like conquerors of the wilderness.}
